news.title: Kolkata: Cracks again in Bowbazar Metro zone buildings
news.para: The addresses included 14G, 15, 19, 17, 1/4 Durga Pithuri Lane. KMRC and ITD Cementation officials shifted at least 50 residents to hotels. KMRC engineers said they were trying to find what caused the new cracks.

news.title: PNB says ready to subscribe to PNB Housing's rights issue if RBI approves
news.para: PNB holds around 32.6% stake in the mortgage lender and it would need to shell out around Rs 800 crore if it subscribes to the latter's capital raising plan.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body officials set to revise rent agreements of 600 properties
news.para: The MC has over 600 properties given on rent or allotment while 28 properties are on lease. These properties are located at prime locations but the officials did not revise the rent for a long time, and it was fixed at a very low price band when allotments were done.

news.title: Notices to 151 Mumbai buildings over fire safety in six months
news.para: ​According to latest data from the Mumbai Fire Brigade, of the 329 buildings which were randomly inspected between November 2021 and April 2022, 151 buildings were issued notices for non-compliance with fire safety measures.

news.title: HIDCO plans to e-auction Alipore land for 99-year lease
news.para: The land parcel, as mentioned in the Hidco notice, has been earmarked by the state government at 1, Thackeray Road and 4, Judges Court Road under KMC ward No 74.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to raze Janta Colony on May 15
news.para: The decision was taken in a meeting held under the chairmanship of deputy commissioner Vinay Pratap Singh. An approval has already been given by UT adviser Dharam Pal.

news.title: RWA seeks camp to resolve errors in Gurugram civic body's new property IDs
news.para: According to the residents, the new property IDs issued have wrong names and addresses and there is a lot of confusion on filing the property tax dues.

news.title: Single-window system to ease house tax filing in Lucknow
news.para: Mayor Sanyukta Bhatia on Wednesday ordered for a single-window system to be put into place for house tax, tax revision, mutations and other tax processes for which residents have to wade through bureaucracy.

news.title: Haryana CM chairs meeting to discuss bottlenecks of Gurugram's Global City
news.para: HSIIDC is building this central business district in Gurgaon as an ecosystem of companies that are into future technology, low-carbon green infrastructure, easy living and skill building. Job generation is another objective.

news.title: Credberg to invest over Rs 1,000 crore in Indian income-producing assets
news.para: Creberg is foraying into investment management and looking to raise its maiden fund Credberg Real estate office opportunities fund 1 (CREOOF-1). The company has already formed a new platform Credberg Investment Management to undertake its foray into the fund business.

news.title: Eight illegal colonies demolished in in Farukhnagar and Mubarakpur
news.para: The illegal colonies were at the initial stage of development. The construction had started on the plots which the developer was in the process to sell.

news.title: Gurugram: Mahira Homes' licence cancelled, buyers in a fix
news.para: Though the DTCP plans to complete the project, keeping the interest of the investors in mind, many homebuyers questioned how the licence was granted to the developer in the first place when fake documents were submitted.

news.title: Sagar Cements posts net loss of Rs 19.15 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: However, its revenue from operations was up 20.12 per cent to Rs 501.72 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 417.65 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.

news.title: New York-listed KE Holdings debuts on Hong Kong stock exchange
news.para: KE's listing follows a similar move by electric vehicle manufacturer Nio Inc in March. In a listing by introduction, a company does not issue new shares or raise fresh capital, unlike a traditional initial public offering (IPO).

news.title: Sunac China misses bond coupon payment as grace period ends: Sources
news.para: Failure to make $29.5 million in interest payments on the October 2023 bond that had been due last month could represent the first offshore default on a public bond by the nation's third-largest developer by sales.
